Global Automotive Electronic Power Steering Market Insights
Automotive Electronic Power Steering Market size was valued at USD 20.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 33.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.2% from 2024 to 2030.

Automotive Electronic Power Steering Market Overview
The global automotive electronic power steering market is projected to grow significantly, with an estimated value of USD 45.5 billion in 2024, expected to reach USD 80.1 billion by 2030, at a CAGR of 10.5%. The increasing demand for energy-efficient and lightweight vehicles, along with the rising adoption of advanced driver-assistance systems (ADAS), are key factors driving this growth. The market is witnessing substantial innovation with advancements in technologies such as steer-by-wire systems and autonomous driving capabilities. Growing concerns for fuel efficiency and environmental sustainability continue to push automotive manufacturers towards the adoption of electric power steering (EPS) systems.

